description:
InterfaceIPv4: Table describing IPv4 interface configurations for various network elements.

dateTime: Timestamp of data record.
Area_Name: Geographic area of the network element.
CellId: Unique identifier of the cell site.
Id2: Duplicate of CellId.
Id3:  Identifier indicating the type of network element or interface.
Id4: Simplified identifier for the network element or interface.
vsDataType: Data type identifier.
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
InterfaceIPv4.encapsulation: Encapsulation details including subnetwork, context, transport, and VLAN port.
InterfaceIPv4.userLabel: User-friendly label for the interface.
InterfaceIPv4.pcpArp: Priority Code Point for ARP.
InterfaceIPv4.aclIngress: Ingress Access Control List configuration.
InterfaceIPv4.mtu: Maximum Transmission Unit size.
InterfaceIPv4.routesHoldDownTimer: Hold-down timer for routing.
InterfaceIPv4.egressQosMarking: Egress QoS marking configuration.
InterfaceIPv4.bfdProfile: BFD profile configuration.
InterfaceIPv4.bfdStaticRoutes: Status of BFD for static routes (enabled/disabled).
InterfaceIPv4.reservedBy: Indication of reservation status.
InterfaceIPv4.routingPolicyIngress: Ingress routing policy configuration.
InterfaceIPv4.arpTimeout: ARP timeout value.
InterfaceIPv4.trackedInterface: Tracked interface information.
InterfaceIPv4.ingressQosMarking: Ingress QoS marking configuration.
InterfaceIPv4.interfaceIPv4Id: Unique identifier for the IPv4 interface.
InterfaceIPv4.aclEgress: Egress Access Control List configuration.
InterfaceIPv4.loopback: Loopback interface status (true/false).
